Review Title: Overall, my stay at the hotel exceeded my expectations and I would highly recommend
Negative Reviews: there were a couple of downsides to my stay. The walls were quite thin, which made it easy to hear noise from neighboring rooms. Additionally, despite reminding staff several times, the shampoo and conditioner were not replenished during my stay, which was a bit disappointing.
Positive Reviews:
The lady at the check in counter was incredibly friendly and welcoming. What impressed me most was that she remembered my name when I arrived to check in, which was a pleasant surprise.  To my delight, I was upgraded to a room with added amenities, including a microwave and a mini-fridge. 

The hotel is perfectly situated in the heart of downtown, making it easy to explore local attractions and restaurants.   

The hotel offers a fantastic range of amenities.  The complimentary beverages  in the lobby were a nice touch, making it easy to unwind after a day of exploring. The laundrette on-site was incredibly convenient.  The inhouse restaurant offered a variety of delicious options, but I must highlight the signature salmon dish which was absolutely divine. The freshness and flavor of the ingredients were evident in every bite, making it one of the best meals I've ever had.  The ambiance of the hotel is inviting with a stylish lobby and there are plenty of cozy seating areas to relax or meet with friends.

Positive Reviews:
Distance to Minute Maid Park is perfect. The price of the room was less than parking at the playoff game. The room was clean and had all of the amenities. The staff was excellent. From the valet to the front desk and checkout everyone was very friendly and helpful. We usually stay with a large chain but this hotel was 1/4 of the price. What a hidden gem! The restaurant, Bistro 7, was very convenient and the food was good. 
We plan to stay here for every downtown event in the future. 
Our entire stay: room, and taxes, valet, and tips was still less than a room at the hotel we usually stay at.

Positive Reviews: The location is incredible! You are right in the heart of downtown and everything is within walking distance. I personally love downtown Houston so I’m probably partial but the location carries really great as far as amenities. It’s a great hotel it’s beautiful the rooms are nice sized. The beds are very very comfortable. The staff was exceptional The front desk staff was so helpful and so accommodating, they were two guys that I cannot remember their names. They were the night staff, and one girl in particular named Julie. That was amazing. They all went above and beyond to be helpful. I had my service dog with me and they were just so accommodating. The only complaint I have is one of the managers that was on during the daytime was so hateful. She spoke to the staff like they were trash. She spoke to the staff like they were idiots. She literally rolled her eyes at me multiple times and had the audacity to talk to me like I was stupid regarding the situation with the elevator after my key been deactivated - in order to access the elevators you must use your key, which I love as far as a safety measure goes, but it’s not convenient when the key has either been deactivated for whatever reason or when you’re trying to check out. I’m going to the front desk three times at this point because he attempted to get the elevator to work for me to go back up and get the rest of my stuff - that last time I was frustrated because it hadn’t worked and this was four times, and she rolled her eyes at me again, and said “ he push the button you just need to be patient and wait!” which wasn’t the case at all because the light was flashing red each time which meant the cards they were using weren’t active. She’s just a horrible person, and an even worse manager, and why she has a job there - i’ll never understand because everyone else was wonderful. She literally stuck out like a sore thumb because everyone was so great while she was really really horrible to everybody.

What appears to have been the original entrance once is now closed off forcing people to enter where the valet stand is and the check in counter is a tiny stand wedged into an alcove in the wall along a skinny hallway instead of out in the openness of the main lobby. This was extremely frustrating having to move to allow other people in and out with bags and carts while waiting to be helped since none of the self check in kiosks were available. Upon checkin a woman was training a new hire and did not even look up to acknowledge us but kept speaking to him about other guests and their payment and room situations - very unprofessional in front of other guests. The rooms are outdated and not in line with the style of the main lobby. The carpet and walls were dirty.

Negative Reviews: There's no complimentary breakfast.
Positive Reviews:
The Location of this hotel was perfect as you can walk to the Theater District, Green District, museums Old Market Square, Little Tranquility Park, Discovery Green Park, Buffalo Bayou, Downtown Aquarium and most of the sites in downtown. We rarely had to use taxi. It is also very close to the light rail system, 

Check-in and check-out is self and quite easy. The reception staff is always there to help you in case you need any assistance.

The room was very spacious, clean, and comfortable and had everything we needed. The room was provided with a TV, mini refrigerator, telephone, tea/coffee maker, iron box and free Wi-Fi.  Bathroom had free toiletries.  

The lobby of this hotel is very huge and looks modern. A business center with newspapers is available. There are plenty of seats with ports for connecting your laptops and mobile phones. The best part of this hotel is that you can enjoy unlimited complimentary snacks and refreshments in the lounge whenever you want. You can fill your water bottles also here.
Club Quarters Hotel in downtown Houston offers a fitness center. The self-service laundry is free of charge, whereas, most of the hotels charge for this service. Unlike in other places, there are plenty of washing machines and dryers, which avoids waiting time. I heard there is no free parking, but, there is parking available nearby, which is charged. There is also valet parking available. 

Table 7 Bistro, the only restaurant inside the hotel, serves American cuisine for breakfast, lunch and dinner. The bartender was extremely friendly and was happy to serve even at the closing hours.

Review Title: Great location for concerts and sporting events
Negative Reviews: Nothing really. System was down for their app you're supposed to be able to use for everything, but that wasn't a problem at all. I was fine with the "old school" check-in with a person and get a key card :) I would note that I ordered food from the restaurant through Yelp/GrubHub that said my order was received, but it actually wasn't, so when I went to pick it up they hadn't even started yet, despite what Yelp said. So just be sure to go in person or check-in with them to be sure they got your order.
Positive Reviews: Spent 1 night in Houston for a concert at 713 Music Hall and this hotel was within walking distance (0.7mi, 15-20m) at a better value than surrounding hotels. Room was clean and comfortable. The room is quite small, at least the single bed rooms, which was fine and even welcomed for me. There was the bed, TV, desk, closet, and bathroom. Definitely snug, but perfectly fine for one or two people for a night or two. Friendly staff on check-in, nice public spot downstairs to meet others in your party, attached restaurant serving breakfast, lunch, and dinner which is very convenient. Parking is in a lot across the street, $25 for 24h with in and out privileges if you talk to the staff and pay in advance. Was a really convenient option, close by, access to the car if you need it. There is also valet. Or you can pick any other lot in the area if you want, but this one was convenient, safe, secure, easy parking. There is free street parking after 6p but seemed like a pain. A lot seems to be the only option if staying in a hotel downtown. Hotel was secure, you need key access for the doors and elevators. Wasn't sure what to expect regarding the safety of the neighborhood, but the theater district is quite nice and walking around at 6p and 11p was perfectly fine (I was there on a Monday so it was quiet, well lit, and not many people out other than some concert goers). Main St. is right around the corner. Plenty of restaurants and Phoenicia Specialty Market is nearby, definitely worth a visit.

Review Title: Shouldn’t qualify as a hotel, hostel is more like it
Negative Reviews: Our experience here was shockingly bad. We booked a room for three guests and we were given a small bed with just one small double bed. We complained and they told us they could bring in a rollaway bed that could never have fit into that room. Finally they upgraded us to a double room with a sofa bed. The sofa bed was not made and when we called to have they make it, they told us the bedding was in the wardrobe and we had to make it ourselves. There was nothing in the wardrobe so we had to ask for the bedding. They brought us a plastic bag with a bottom sheet a pillow and a blanket. We had to call again for a top sheet. Being forced to make your own bed and having to call multiple times to get the bedding set at 11pm at a four star hotel? Absolutely ridiculous. Very unhelpful and condescending staff as well. Would not recommend club quarters to anyone.

I will relate my story in full, so any potential customers know what to expect. I had booked my stay for five nights and fully paid in advance. Two days before arrival, my flight was cancelled last-minute and I immediately let the hotel know through the Booking.com app indicating the new arrival date. Noticing that they had not replied after 24 hours, I sent another message asking for confirmation they had received the first text. No reply. When I arrived in Houston the receptionist said that they considered it 'no show', but I had the full booking documentation, including the messages they had ignored. So I was given the room I had booked and at the same time told that an amount of $150 would be additionally pre-authorised to cover for potential damages and refunded upon check-out. Ok, fine. One day into my stay I see that the pre-authorised amount had gone up to a total of $346.89, with no explanation. I immediately asked at the reception and was given an opaque answer along the lines that more needed to be pre-authorised, and there was nothing to worry about since I would be refunded at the end of the stay, within two to three working days (a receptionist called Diana). I trusted them. Back in Europe I received an invoice that made little sense charging me twice for 'no show' and multiple taxes (basically they charged no show although I had timely communicated the late check in). They are obviously not planning to refund anything. Please do not trust these people with your credit card details, and go somewhere else. I have currently asked Booking.com to solve the issue and I am waiting for them to process the request.

Review Title: Not the best, but good for a 1 or 2 night stay if you don’t want to spend a lot.
Negative Reviews:
VERY thin walls. Was woken up at around 3:30am by an argument between a male and female in the room next to us (I understand this isn’t the hotel’s fault). Later that morning, I was woken up by them again, but they were having a normal conversation this time. The morning after, which was the morning we checked out, we were woken up by the housekeeper cleaning that same room next to us. 
The banging and noise was excessive. We could hear her walking through the room, cleaning the toilet, putting items away or cleaning drawers.. whatever it was. The amount of times this one room’s door was slammed was incredible. I’m not exaggerating when I say it was probably a dozen times. Twice, something was slammed or banged so hard that it shook the adjoining wall, which is where the bed is set up. It was extremely frustrating. 
The restroom and shower could be much cleaner.  There was hair stuck on the restroom wall, along with some makeup from previous visitors. The shower looked like it needed a good scrub on the walls, floor, and shower head. The water pressure was great but only half of the shower head had water coming out of it. The holes on the other half were clogged.
The charging port installed on the table did not work and neither did the phone. This was annoying when I woke up the first morning and grabbed my Apple Watch expecting it to be fully charged, but it was dead. 
The bed and pillows were comfortable. We only had 2 pillows on our bed. I thought this was weird because usually there are 4. I’m sure if I would’ve requested an extra pillow or two (I like to sleep with my legs propped on a pillow) the hotel would have sent some up, but we never bothered with it. 
When we did interact with staff, they were helpful and friendly.
Positive Reviews: Good rate for a holiday weekend.
